CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 27, 1958, pg. A1, reads: "Protest Conditions - This delegation of residents of the Somerset St. are met at the office of 12th Ward Alderman and Democratic Ward Chairman August R. Costa on Lincoln Ave., Monday night, and protested the conditions of Somerset St. and other conditions in ward. Seated: Mr. and Mrs. R. J. Cousar, Mrs. D. Wheeler and Mrs. R. Stokes. Standing: R. Bagley, J.B. Walker, Mrs. J. Thomas, S. Sims, J. Thomas, L. Banks, J. Rizzo and the Rev. E. Roberts. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Somerset Street residents, including seated from left: Mr. and Mrs. R. J. Cousar, Mrs. D. Wheeler, and Mrs. R. Stokes; standing: R. Bagley, J.B. Walker, Mrs. J. Thomas, S. Sims, J. Thomas, L. Banks, J. Rizzo, and Rev. E. Roberts, in office of 12th Ward Alderman August R. Costa, Lincoln Avenue
